data.chText: 这一事件究竟是什么时候发生的？
data.enText: When exactly did the incident occur?

data.chText: 发生了一件出乎意料的事。

data.enText: to exist or be found somewhere

before.enText: of an idea or a thought

data.chText: 这个主意是他在梦中想到的。
data.enText: The idea occurred to him in a dream.

data.chText: 他没有想到自己的妻子有婚外情。
data.enText: It didn't occur to him that his wife was having an affair.
It didn't occur to her to ask for help.

simple_means.memory_skill: oc 加强 + cur 跑，引申为“发生” → 发生；出现

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，多用于偶然事件。

ex.chText: 昨天发生了一起严重的交通事故。
ex.enText: A serious traffic accident occurred/happened yesterday.

synonyms.bx: 可用于偶然事件或计划之事，可与 happen 换用。

ex.chText: 中国发生了翻天覆地的变化。
ex.enText: Great changes have taken place in China.

ex.chText: 庆祝游行定于星期日举行，风雨无阻。
ex.enText: The parade will take place on Sunday, rain or shine.

synonyms.bx: 主要用于事先计划好的事情。

before.enText: of an idea or a thought

data.chText: 这个主意是他在梦中想到的。
data.enText: The idea occurred to him in a dream.

data.chText: 他没有想到自己的妻子有婚外情。
data.enText: It didn't occur to him that his wife was having an affair.
It didn't occur to her to ask for help.

example: The meeting took place off without an incidence
It occurred to me that we should hire another secretary
A great idea then came to her
precious stones occur in a large area in Brazil

example.ex: If headaches only occur at night, lack of fresh air and oxygen is often the cause...
example.tran: 如果只是在晚上头疼，那常常是由于缺乏新鲜空气和氧气的缘故。

example.ex: The crash occurred when the crew shut down the wrong engine...
example.tran: 机务人员关错了引擎，随即飞机坠毁。

example.ex: In March 1770, there occurred what became known as the Boston Massacre.
example.tran: 1770年3月在那里发生了后来闻名的波士顿惨案。

value.def: When something occurs in a particular place, it exists or is present there.

example.ex: The cattle disease occurs more or less anywhere in Africa where the fly occurs...
example.tran: 在非洲凡是有这种蝇虫的地方，几乎都会出现这一牛病。

example.ex: These snails do not occur on low-lying coral islands or atolls.
example.tran: 在地势低平的珊瑚岛或环礁上没有这种螺。

value.def: If a thought or idea occurs to you, you suddenly think of it or realize it.

example.ex: It did not occur to me to check my insurance policy...
example.tran: 我没有想到要核实我的保险单条款。

example.ex: It occurred to me that I could have the book sent to me...
example.tran: 我想到可以让人把书寄给我。

example.ex: The same idea had occurred to Elizabeth.
example.tran: 伊丽莎白也想到了这个主意。

value.tran: （想法或主意）被想到，被想起，浮现于脑海中

trans: 突然杀；忽然杀；屠杀；俄然杀

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to run 跑 , 引申为“发生”
rootsaffixes.title: cur(r), curs, cour(i), cours
